author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring 1 1/2 cups @salted water{1 1/2%cups} to a boil in a small #pot. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Halve @lime{1}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Pick half the @basil{1/2%oz}(leaves picked from stems and roughly chopped, save the rest for garnish) and roughly chop (save the rest for garnish). Mince @chili pepper{1}(ribs and seeds removed for less heat).

Crush @peanuts{1%oz} inside their bag with a #mallet or heavy pan. Once water boils, add @jade rice{3/4%cup} to #pot. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, ~{13-15%minutes}.

Toss @green beans{6%oz} on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast in #oven until lightly crisped, about ~{12%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan over medium heat. Add shallot, garlic, and as much chili as you like. Cook, tossing, until softened and fragrant, about ~{3%minutes}. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and increase heat to high, breaking up meat into small pieces. Cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Remove #pan from heat. Stir in @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, @soy sauce{1%tbsp}, chopped basil, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in a squeeze or two of @lime{1} (to taste).

Divide rice between plates, then arrange stir-fry on top. Sprinkle with peanuts. Tear remaining basil leaves from stems and scatter over top. Serve with green beans on the side.

> The ground pork topped with peanuts and aromatic basil creates a symphony of flavor.